Subject: Fix isUpcoming=true on all lockup-video entries

The new LockupViewModelParser introduced by PR #5736 sets
`premiere_timestamp: Time.unix(0)` for all lockup-video entries.

This is non-nil, so `SearchVideo#upcoming?`
(at src/invidious/helpers/serialized_yt_data.cr:150) returns true,
which serializes as `"isUpcoming": true` in API responses.

API clients that hide upcoming premieres from feeds (Yattee, etc.)
therefore filter every channel video out of the subscription feed
and channel pages.

The legacy VideoRendererParser correctly passes through the
*parsed* premiere_timestamp value, which is nil for normal videos.
This patch matches that semantic for the new parser.

Note: ReelItemRendererParser and ShortsLockupViewModelParser have
the same pre-existing pattern but aren't fixed here — the former
is effectively dead code, and shorts go through a separate UI path
in Yattee. Worth raising as a follow-up upstream but out of scope
for unbreaking the feed today.

---
 src/invidious/yt_backend/extractors.cr | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/invidious/yt_backend/extractors.cr b/src/invidious/yt_backend/extractors.cr
--- a/src/invidious/yt_backend/extractors.cr
+++ b/src/invidious/yt_backend/extractors.cr
@@ -677,7 +677,7 @@ private module Parsers
           views:              view_count,
           description_html:   "",
           length_seconds:     0,
-          premiere_timestamp: Time.unix(0),
+          premiere_timestamp: nil,
           author_verified:    false,
           author_thumbnail:   nil,
           badges:             VideoBadges::None,
